1
00:00:20,050 --> 00:00:24,000
I ask for Princess Suphankalaya to be my royal consort.

2
00:00:24,600 --> 00:00:27,160
They tried to escape. We were merely securing them, Your Highness.

3
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:28,920
Securing them? You are slaughtering my people!

4
00:00:29,850 --> 00:00:31,700
Are we still brothers?

5
00:00:32,240 --> 00:00:33,760
If in the days to come,

6
00:00:33,957 --> 00:00:36,800
Ayutthaya no longer bows to Hongsawadi,

7
00:00:37,850 --> 00:00:40,280
would you still have the heart to call me brother?

8
00:00:41,040 --> 00:00:44,080
With such words, rebellion must already be in his heart.

9
00:00:44,210 --> 00:00:45,211
How dare you!

10
00:00:46,137 --> 00:00:47,840
I shall take this matter into my own hands.

11
00:00:48,560 --> 00:00:50,190
So, would you have me train with the lance instead?

12
00:00:50,272 --> 00:00:52,760
Had I possessed the mastery that you do,

13
00:00:53,120 --> 00:00:55,482
I would never bow my head to the Burmese.

14
00:00:55,970 --> 00:00:56,971
What of Prince Nares?

15
00:00:57,010 --> 00:00:58,243
I have not seen his face for many suns now.

16
00:00:58,403 --> 00:01:01,560
That you have come to master the Mon blades under my tutelage,

17
00:01:02,270 --> 00:01:04,240
If this truth should ever reach the ears of King Bayinnaung,

18
00:01:04,443 --> 00:01:06,800
Our lives, both yours and mine, shall be forfeit.

19
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:08,880
Since you've graced us with your presence,

20
00:01:09,320 --> 00:01:11,000
Why not step out from the shadows and face me?

21
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:25,720
Why do you follow me?

22
00:01:28,250 --> 00:01:31,720
If I hadn't followed, how would I have known?

23
00:01:35,277 --> 00:01:39,040
Did you not swear to King Bayinnaung

24
00:01:40,160 --> 00:01:41,880
never to touch a blade again until your dying day?

25
00:01:46,357 --> 00:01:50,840
My hands have yet to touch a single blade.

26
00:01:55,080 --> 00:01:56,520
A man of the cloth,

27
00:01:57,920 --> 00:02:00,120
yet you use a silver tongue to save your neck.

28
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,560
I wonder

29
00:02:06,480 --> 00:02:08,480
how would my Grandfather

30
00:02:09,280 --> 00:02:10,800
judge this wisdom of yours?

31
00:02:28,960 --> 00:02:30,800
What are you two plotting?

32
00:04:00,480 --> 00:04:02,781
I have bought you the time I can.

33
00:04:03,640 --> 00:04:04,750
What follows now

34
00:04:06,880 --> 00:04:09,440
lies solely in your hands.

35
00:04:28,320 --> 00:04:29,642
No one knows

36
00:04:31,017 --> 00:04:32,520
I came to find you here

37
00:04:34,270 --> 00:04:35,800
Kill me now,

38
00:04:36,840 --> 00:04:40,120
burn my body in this temple's flames

39
00:04:42,177 --> 00:04:43,840
And the world will never know.

40
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,550
I seek no man's life.

41
00:04:49,040 --> 00:04:51,600
My only hope is to see Ayutthaya free once more.

42
00:04:53,041 --> 00:04:55,800
The Mon styles the Monk taught you.

43
00:04:58,440 --> 00:05:00,210
You mean to use them against us, don't you?

44
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:05,160
My blade

45
00:05:06,737 --> 00:05:08,320
is reserved for my enemies alone.

46
00:05:51,783 --> 00:05:53,640
And you, Brother, are not my enemy.

47
00:06:08,763 --> 00:06:09,764
Do you

48
00:06:10,843 --> 00:06:12,960
not fear hat I might tell Grandfather everything?

49
00:06:14,810 --> 00:06:16,760
Tell him whatever you wish.

50
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:19,760
I have given my word

51
00:06:20,840 --> 00:06:22,400
not to harm you.

52
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:25,240
And I shall keep it.

53
00:06:59,783 --> 00:07:01,440
Whatever follows from this moment,

54
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:06,040
I leave it to the hands of fate and my own karma.

55
00:07:15,870 --> 00:07:18,000
The Kingdom of Pagan is vast beyond measure.

56
00:07:20,377 --> 00:07:22,520
Ayutthaya was never truly my home.

57
00:07:25,523 --> 00:07:27,200
If I were the Lord of Hongsawadi,

58
00:07:27,720 --> 00:07:29,560
I would restore Ayutthaya to you this very instant.

59
00:07:39,483 --> 00:07:43,200
It is a pity that you are not.

60
00:07:49,123 --> 00:07:50,124
Nares.

61
00:07:52,850 --> 00:07:54,280
I feel for you.

62
00:07:55,630 --> 00:07:58,120
And I will not stand in the way of your lessons.

63
00:07:59,430 --> 00:08:00,880
But if ever you

64
00:08:02,280 --> 00:08:04,600
harbor ill intent toward my Father or my Grandfather,

65
00:08:06,077 --> 00:08:09,488
from that moment, we are brothers no more.

66
00:08:17,803 --> 00:08:20,604
From that day forth,

67
00:08:21,040 --> 00:08:23,320
brother and I became strangers.

68
00:08:24,080 --> 00:08:25,400
Until the day

69
00:08:25,681 --> 00:08:27,920
a grand ceremony was held in Hongsawadi.

70
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:30,921
[Hongsawadi Palace]

71
00:08:42,650 --> 00:08:47,160
It was the ear-piercing ceremony of Minye Kyawswa,

72
00:08:47,723 --> 00:08:49,160
The second son

73
00:08:49,543 --> 00:08:51,920
of Phra Maha Uparaja Jaisingh,

74
00:08:52,603 --> 00:08:54,560
and the younger brother of Mingyi Swa.

75
00:09:38,520 --> 00:09:41,040
[Princess Yaza Datu Kalaya, daughter of King Bayinnaung]

76
00:09:41,100 --> 00:09:44,000
[Born of his second Queen Consort]

77
00:09:57,160 --> 00:09:59,680
I must humbly beg your forgiveness for my late arrival.

78
00:10:00,140 --> 00:10:01,320
You have just returned from her retreat.

79
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:05,760
Who would dare complain?

80
00:10:06,680 --> 00:10:08,800
I feared you wouldn't come.

81
00:10:10,777 --> 00:10:12,080
Today is a momentous day.

82
00:10:12,520 --> 00:10:14,440
I could never have stayed away.

83
00:10:32,800 --> 00:10:33,801
Royal Aunt.

84
00:12:06,760 --> 00:12:08,290
Once the ear-piercing is complete,

85
00:12:08,837 --> 00:12:10,280
you are considered a man grown.

86
00:12:10,710 --> 00:12:11,920
Minye Kyawswa,

87
00:12:12,880 --> 00:12:17,081
I bless you with long life and enduring spirit.

88
00:12:17,563 --> 00:12:19,520
May you be granted victory.

89
00:12:22,937 --> 00:12:25,560
I am deeply honored, Your Highness.

90
00:12:43,883 --> 00:12:44,884
Well…

91
00:12:45,977 --> 00:12:47,160
Captive.

92
00:13:14,160 --> 00:13:16,320
[Borderlands Forest – Outside Prome]

93
00:13:28,590 --> 00:13:29,591
Who is that?

94
00:13:50,800 --> 00:13:52,801
[The Pavilion of Princess Suphankalaya]

95
00:14:00,320 --> 00:14:02,640
I have an urgent matter to report to the King.

96
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:09,001
His Majesty is dining with the Junior Queen.

97
00:14:09,040 --> 00:14:10,041
Move!

98
00:14:19,352 --> 00:14:21,500
Phra Maha Uparaja has arrived, Your Majesty.

99
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:34,640
I crave your royal pardon, Father.

100
00:14:35,100 --> 00:14:36,600
A situation has arisen in Prome.

101
00:14:36,997 --> 00:14:40,280
King Thado Dhamma Yaza has sent an urgent dispatch to Your Majesty.

102
00:14:40,563 --> 00:14:43,280
I must humbly request an audience to present it at once.

103
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:45,600
What has happened in Prome?

104
00:14:46,400 --> 00:14:47,880
The Mohnyin rebels are invading.

105
00:14:48,401 --> 00:14:51,881
Royal Uncle sent a messenger to Hongsawadi for aid,

106
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:55,560
but they were ambushed by Mohnyin soldiers along the way.

107
00:14:55,877 --> 00:14:58,320
The only survivor succumbed to his wounds shortly after arriving, Your Majesty.

108
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,160
What does the dispatch say?

109
00:15:00,720 --> 00:15:02,480
Binnya Dala, speak at once.

110
00:15:07,807 --> 00:15:12,760
I, Nanda Yawda, prostrate myself at the feet

111
00:15:13,120 --> 00:15:15,920
of my royal elder brother, King Bayinnaung.

112
00:15:16,520 --> 00:15:17,620
At this moment,

113
00:15:18,363 --> 00:15:19,840
the Mohnyin have become insolent and bold.

114
00:15:20,440 --> 00:15:22,000
They have sent forces to pillage and plunder

115
00:15:22,130 --> 00:15:24,760
across the borders of Prome without a single day's respite.

116
00:15:25,470 --> 00:15:27,600
Though Prome has deployed troops to resist them,

117
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:29,520
we are vastly outnumbered.

118
00:15:30,080 --> 00:15:32,560
I, therefore, humbly submit this request for your royal assistance.

119
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:36,280
I await your gracious command, Your Majesty.

120
00:15:48,560 --> 00:15:49,561
I crave your royal pardon, Father.

121
00:15:50,360 --> 00:15:52,560
The Mohnyin are conducting these raids merely to test our strength.

122
00:15:53,043 --> 00:15:54,240
If we do not suppress them now,

123
00:15:54,497 --> 00:15:56,640
they will surely launch a full-scale invasion to seize Prome.

124
00:15:59,080 --> 00:16:00,600
A single Mohnyin soldier

125
00:16:01,320 --> 00:16:03,640
is a match for ten of our own.

126
00:16:05,640 --> 00:16:07,160
They are of immense stature

127
00:16:08,400 --> 00:16:09,401
and possessing great strength.

128
00:16:10,640 --> 00:16:12,880
Moreover, they favor the use of poisoned darts.

129
00:16:13,560 --> 00:16:14,841
If we do not march to their aid,

130
00:16:16,200 --> 00:16:17,720
Prome will surely fall into their hands.

131
00:16:18,469 --> 00:16:19,470
I crave your royal pardon, Your Majesty.

132
00:16:20,080 --> 00:16:22,160
The Mohnyin are merely savages.

133
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:26,750
It is beneath your dignity to lead the Great Army against them yourself.

134
00:16:26,850 --> 00:16:27,851
Your Majesty.

135
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:32,320
Then who shall volunteer?

136
00:16:35,543 --> 00:16:36,800
Whom do you see fit for the task?

137
00:16:38,080 --> 00:16:40,320
With all due respect, Your Majesty.

138
00:16:42,680 --> 00:16:45,320
The Mohnyin dwell in remote, desolate lands.

139
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:49,120
I agree with Binnya Dala,

140
00:16:50,817 --> 00:16:52,480
it is beneath your dignity

141
00:16:52,960 --> 00:16:54,760
to lead this campaign yourself.

142
00:16:55,350 --> 00:16:58,000
However, whoever goes to suppress the Mohnyin in your stead

143
00:16:58,680 --> 00:17:01,080
must be a warrior of formidable skill.

144
00:17:03,943 --> 00:17:05,720
And who, in your view, is the right man for the task?

145
00:17:07,663 --> 00:17:10,320
The one who marches to crush the Mohnyin rebels

146
00:17:11,280 --> 00:17:14,600
and rescue the King of Prome, your royal brother,

147
00:17:15,560 --> 00:17:16,837
will have done

148
00:17:17,150 --> 00:17:19,280
a great service to the Toungoo Dynasty.

149
00:17:19,680 --> 00:17:23,600
As your representative, he will project Hongsawadi's might

150
00:17:23,910 --> 00:17:26,240
for all to see.

151
00:17:26,883 --> 00:17:28,100
It is, therefore,

152
00:17:28,800 --> 00:17:31,720
a duty of the highest honor.

153
00:17:34,543 --> 00:17:36,080
I believe

154
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:38,600
the most suitable man for this task is…

155
00:17:38,777 --> 00:17:40,840
It is Mingyi Swa, my own son.

156
00:17:44,683 --> 00:17:46,100
Mingyi Swa?

157
00:17:48,590 --> 00:17:49,591
Yes, Your Majesty.

158
00:18:06,720 --> 00:18:09,160
Did Grandfather truly command that I go?

159
00:18:10,440 --> 00:18:12,800
Even if he didn't command it, you should have volunteered.

160
00:18:14,217 --> 00:18:16,280
Or would you rather let someone else snatch the victory

161
00:18:16,357 --> 00:18:18,360
and claim all the glory for themselves?

162
00:18:20,217 --> 00:18:21,880
If I win, so be it.

163
00:18:23,857 --> 00:18:25,760
- But what if I do not win?
- What is this?

164
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:29,001
Afraid before you've even laid eyes on the enemy?

165
00:18:30,100 --> 00:18:33,840
Father, I go to save lives,

166
00:18:34,170 --> 00:18:35,520
not to boast of my courage.

167
00:18:36,757 --> 00:18:39,360
In this war, if we fall to the Mohnyin,

168
00:18:40,200 --> 00:18:43,101
If we fail, those in Prome who trust us will suffer and perish.

169
00:18:49,257 --> 00:18:51,000
If you are so afraid,

170
00:18:52,330 --> 00:18:54,442
then send the captive in your place to die instead.

171
00:18:54,690 --> 00:18:57,360
You! Always such sharp, bitter words.

172
00:18:57,920 --> 00:18:59,480
I've a good mind to give you a taste of the cane!

173
00:19:02,683 --> 00:19:04,360
[Mingyi Naung]

174
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:06,401
[Phra Maha Uparaja Jaisingh's youngest son]

175
00:19:08,120 --> 00:19:11,320
The Crown Prince fell for my silver tongue.

176
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:15,640
He saw the General’s rank like a tiger sees prey

177
00:19:16,243 --> 00:19:17,560
and lunged for it.

178
00:19:21,203 --> 00:19:23,920
But only when the tiger feeds that meat to his cub

179
00:19:24,560 --> 00:19:28,560
will he realize the meat is poisoned.

180
00:19:29,720 --> 00:19:30,960
Why do you speak so, Sister?

181
00:19:31,480 --> 00:19:34,560
If Mingyi Swa rises to the rank of General, what then?

182
00:19:35,170 --> 00:19:37,040
The Mohnyin are far more dangerous than you think.

183
00:19:37,640 --> 00:19:39,480
Not only are they many,

184
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:44,000
but they use crossbows with poisoned bolts.

185
00:19:44,960 --> 00:19:47,880
One scratch is a certain death.

186
00:19:50,320 --> 00:19:51,920
Even King Bayinnaung himself

187
00:19:52,280 --> 00:19:54,377
does not dare to underestimate the Mohnyin army.

188
00:19:55,870 --> 00:19:57,040
Do not overthink this.

189
00:19:57,800 --> 00:20:00,040
You shall lead the army in your Grandfather’s stead,

190
00:20:00,560 --> 00:20:03,561
winning victory and bringing glory to your name

191
00:20:04,080 --> 00:20:05,762
just as I once did.

192
00:20:10,570 --> 00:20:12,040
You are the Grandson of the King,

193
00:20:12,800 --> 00:20:16,240
my own son, and a Prince of Hongsawadi.

194
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:20,440
If you cannot best a captive from Ayutthaya, you aren't fit to have been born.

195
00:20:22,400 --> 00:20:26,520
Initially, I intended to lure Jaisingh into volunteering himself with my words.

196
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:28,321
But I miscalculated.

197
00:20:29,120 --> 00:20:32,920
Instead, he is sending his own son straight to his death.

198
00:21:10,530 --> 00:21:11,531
Let go of me!

199
00:21:12,077 --> 00:21:13,078
Let go of me!

200
00:21:13,192 --> 00:21:14,193
Stop!

201
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:16,160
I told you to stop.

202
00:21:19,643 --> 00:21:21,644
This cane was given to me by Grandfather!

203
00:21:22,200 --> 00:21:25,760
I have Grandfather's leave to strike anyone who harms Prince Nares.

204
00:21:26,880 --> 00:21:28,400
If anyone wants to test me, come forward.

205
00:21:30,200 --> 00:21:31,440
You want a taste?

206
00:21:34,280 --> 00:21:35,281
How about you?

207
00:21:54,280 --> 00:21:57,281
From now on, they won't dare bully you anymore.

208
00:22:04,040 --> 00:22:06,360
Does this cane truly belong to King Bayinnaung?

209
00:22:11,623 --> 00:22:13,960
Not at all, I lied.

210
00:22:15,880 --> 00:22:17,040
But don't you worry.

211
00:22:17,360 --> 00:22:21,040
None of them would ever dare ask Grandfather if it's true or not.

212
00:22:28,423 --> 00:22:30,520
To falsely claim the King's name

213
00:22:31,160 --> 00:22:32,680
is a grave offense.

214
00:22:35,303 --> 00:22:36,304
Child or not

215
00:22:37,440 --> 00:22:39,640
even as my own grandson, you must be punished.

216
00:22:44,550 --> 00:22:45,551
Your Majesty,

217
00:22:46,817 --> 00:22:48,700
Brother lied only to protect me.

218
00:22:49,920 --> 00:22:51,920
I ask to receive the punishment in his stead.

219
00:22:53,550 --> 00:22:54,551
Your Majesty,

220
00:22:55,360 --> 00:22:56,761
If Prince Nares is to be punished,

221
00:22:57,200 --> 00:22:59,280
I ask to be punished alongside him.

222
00:23:29,270 --> 00:23:32,920
This Sword of Absolute Authority represents me.

223
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:35,923
I grant you supreme power over the army.

224
00:23:37,183 --> 00:23:38,880
Reward those who serve with merit,

225
00:23:39,497 --> 00:23:41,720
and behead those who fail.

226
00:23:58,280 --> 00:24:02,080
Devote yourself to this war and bring back victory.

227
00:24:05,400 --> 00:24:06,440
I humbly accept, Your Majesty.

228
00:24:07,480 --> 00:24:09,320
I shall fight this war with all my strength

229
00:24:09,723 --> 00:24:11,050
and every ounce of my ability.

230
00:24:25,057 --> 00:24:26,960
By your royal grace, Your Majesty,

231
00:24:27,103 --> 00:24:29,000
Prince Nares requests an audience.

232
00:24:32,343 --> 00:24:33,344
Send him in.

233
00:24:47,520 --> 00:24:49,240
By your royal grace, Your Majesty,

234
00:24:49,880 --> 00:24:52,881
I humbly volunteer to join the campaign with Mingyi Swa.

235
00:24:54,400 --> 00:24:57,960
Your Majesty has already appointed Mingyi Swa as General.

236
00:24:58,143 --> 00:25:01,320
I only ask to fight by his side as a common soldier.

237
00:25:01,657 --> 00:25:03,440
I seek no rank or title, Your Majesty.

238
00:25:04,880 --> 00:25:05,881
Good.

239
00:25:07,143 --> 00:25:09,823
Prince Nares has the heart to serve this kingdom.

240
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:11,960
I am grateful for that.

241
00:25:13,200 --> 00:25:16,201
I hereby appoint Prince Nares as Vice General,

242
00:25:16,920 --> 00:25:19,360
to assist Mingyi Swa in crushing the Mohnyin rebellion.

243
00:25:24,783 --> 00:25:26,000
I humbly accept Your Majesty's command.

244
00:25:27,640 --> 00:25:29,920
I grant you both our blessing.

245
00:25:30,920 --> 00:25:33,400
May you succeed in all your endeavors.

246
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:35,800
Should you return in victory,

247
00:25:36,720 --> 00:25:38,920
I shall bestow upon you both the most magnificent of rewards.

248
00:25:45,320 --> 00:25:46,321
- Yes, Your Majesty.
- Yes, Your Majesty.

249
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:51,441
What did you say?

250
00:25:52,160 --> 00:25:54,640
- Prince Nares is going to war?
- Yes, Your Highness.

251
00:25:55,600 --> 00:25:56,601
Who gave that order?

252
00:25:57,600 --> 00:26:01,200
Khun Phra Nai reports that the Prince volunteered himself, Your Highness.

253
00:26:02,120 --> 00:26:04,440
He refused to listen to anyone's warnings.

254
00:26:07,520 --> 00:26:08,560
Your Highness.

255
00:26:09,842 --> 00:26:11,080
Your Highness.

256
00:26:13,183 --> 00:26:14,240
Your Highness.

257
00:26:14,530 --> 00:26:16,360
- Your Highness.
- Your Highness.

258
00:26:17,637 --> 00:26:18,760
Your Highness.

259
00:26:20,550 --> 00:26:21,551
Your Highness.

260
00:26:23,120 --> 00:26:25,040
Is Princess Suphankalaya with child?

261
00:26:25,800 --> 00:26:28,680
Yes, Your Highness. The inner court is buzzing with the news.

262
00:26:29,080 --> 00:26:32,360
The Junior Queen is three months along.

263
00:26:32,637 --> 00:26:35,920
King Bayinnaung is overjoyed.

264
00:26:41,717 --> 00:26:44,130
He was already pleased enough with Prince Nares volunteering for war.

265
00:26:45,003 --> 00:26:46,840
Now that the Junior Queen is pregnant,

266
00:26:47,103 --> 00:26:49,250
he will surely favor both siblings even more.

267
00:26:52,390 --> 00:26:56,160
Must we truly accept these captives as our own kin?

268
00:27:02,043 --> 00:27:03,280
Minye Kyawswa.

269
00:27:12,090 --> 00:27:14,041
You must go forth to do battle alongside your brother.

270
00:27:15,360 --> 00:27:16,361
Huh?

271
00:27:19,040 --> 00:27:21,241
Father, what would you have me do?

272
00:27:29,720 --> 00:27:31,720
[The Frontier Forest of Mohnyin]

273
00:29:19,580 --> 00:29:20,720
Go and take his head!

274
00:30:35,857 --> 00:30:36,858
Brother.

275
00:30:37,197 --> 00:30:38,198
Brother.

276
00:30:38,663 --> 00:30:39,664
Brother.

277
00:30:39,970 --> 00:30:40,971
I am fine.

278
00:30:46,920 --> 00:30:47,921
Kill him!

279
00:31:20,880 --> 00:31:21,881
Nares!

280
00:32:10,881 --> 00:32:12,640
Drink! To our victory!

281
00:32:12,850 --> 00:32:14,800
To our victory!

282
00:32:20,330 --> 00:32:23,520
Drink! To the end of the war!

283
00:32:23,757 --> 00:32:25,880
To the end of the war!

284
00:32:27,383 --> 00:32:28,880
It is truly my honor

285
00:32:29,200 --> 00:32:30,537
to fight alongside you.

286
00:32:30,630 --> 00:32:33,440
Once Hongsawadi prevails over the Mohnyin,

287
00:32:34,280 --> 00:32:35,720
you must use this poison

288
00:32:35,997 --> 00:32:39,360
assassinate Prince Nares. Ensure he does not return alive.

289
00:32:39,760 --> 00:32:41,520
To kill a commander during battle

290
00:32:41,840 --> 00:32:43,160
carries the death penalty.

291
00:32:43,600 --> 00:32:45,100
You must let no one know.

292
00:32:46,320 --> 00:32:47,520
Be careful.

293
00:32:49,650 --> 00:32:50,651
Yes, Father.

294
00:32:55,510 --> 00:32:56,720
Bottoms up, Your Highness!

295
00:32:57,800 --> 00:32:59,400
Bottoms up?

296
00:33:00,370 --> 00:33:01,371
Stop.

297
00:33:05,040 --> 00:33:06,141
It is empty.

298
00:33:12,720 --> 00:33:14,040
It is so festive out there.

299
00:33:15,743 --> 00:33:17,744
Why do you not go out and join their celebration?

300
00:33:22,040 --> 00:33:23,520
Wait until my wounds have healed first.

301
00:33:26,617 --> 00:33:29,920
If I force myself out now, I fear I will catch a fever.

302
00:33:32,960 --> 00:33:35,040
Prince Nares has taken the enemy's head himself.

303
00:33:36,400 --> 00:33:39,600
You are the Commander, yet you do not join the celebration?

304
00:33:40,120 --> 00:33:41,680
The troops will surely lose heart.

305
00:33:46,410 --> 00:33:48,517
Go out and drink a single toast, that would be enough.

306
00:34:40,510 --> 00:34:41,600
This cup is for you.

307
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:46,200
I have mixed it with water to weaken the strength of the alcohol.

308
00:34:50,600 --> 00:34:53,480
Your shoulder is injured. I shall hold it for you.

309
00:35:07,777 --> 00:35:08,960
Why are you so still?

310
00:35:16,057 --> 00:35:17,098
Bottoms up.

311
00:35:18,203 --> 00:35:19,204
Brother.

312
00:35:19,977 --> 00:35:20,978
Brother.

313
00:35:24,037 --> 00:35:25,120
Do you feel any better now?

314
00:35:26,800 --> 00:35:27,920
A lot better now.

315
00:35:31,640 --> 00:35:33,400
I heard the sounds of joy,

316
00:35:35,003 --> 00:35:37,080
so I wished to come out and celebrate our victory with you all.

317
00:35:42,790 --> 00:35:44,040
This cup is for you.

318
00:35:56,830 --> 00:35:58,520
I wish to drink to Prince Nares,

319
00:35:59,577 --> 00:36:01,880
the Vice Commander who defeated the Mohnyin general

320
00:36:02,337 --> 00:36:04,240
and brought victory to us all!

321
00:36:06,240 --> 00:36:07,241
Wait.

322
00:36:12,437 --> 00:36:14,480
General, your words are not quite right.

323
00:36:15,680 --> 00:36:17,600
Our victory over the Mohnyin army

324
00:36:18,322 --> 00:36:20,640
was achieved through the skill of every single one of us, was it not?

325
00:36:25,553 --> 00:36:26,554
Therefore,

326
00:36:28,343 --> 00:36:30,160
I wish to drink to all of us!

327
00:37:02,930 --> 00:37:04,360
You have been slashed by a blade like that,

328
00:37:05,617 --> 00:37:07,080
yet you still insist on coming out to drink and celebrate?

329
00:37:09,463 --> 00:37:10,600
It is already healed, Your Highness.

330
00:37:13,197 --> 00:37:14,198
Continue the celebration as you please.

331
00:37:22,583 --> 00:37:23,584
Carry on.

332
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:25,361
Yes, Your Highness.

333
00:37:28,470 --> 00:37:29,471
Nares!

334
00:37:31,063 --> 00:37:32,064
Nares!

335
00:37:32,910 --> 00:37:33,911
Nares!

336
00:37:35,580 --> 00:37:38,000
You, take Nares inside the tent.

337
00:37:49,797 --> 00:37:50,798
Nares!

338
00:37:56,330 --> 00:37:57,331
Nares!

339
00:37:58,277 --> 00:37:59,797
Nares! Nares!

340
00:38:00,043 --> 00:38:02,200
Face pale, lips blue, just like one poisoned.

341
00:38:03,443 --> 00:38:04,445
It must be so.

342
00:38:05,477 --> 00:38:07,360
Today, the arrows rained down like a monsoon.

343
00:38:08,383 --> 00:38:11,520
Perhaps he was struck by the Mohnyin's poison without even realizing it.

344
00:38:13,200 --> 00:38:14,880
Mohnyin poison uses Strophanthus.

345
00:38:16,017 --> 00:38:17,600
It acts instantly,

346
00:38:18,403 --> 00:38:19,520
not this late.

347
00:38:22,350 --> 00:38:24,920
Even if struck, he should be fine.

348
00:38:26,520 --> 00:38:29,240
- Why is that?
- Our Grandfather once fought them.D357

349
00:38:30,240 --> 00:38:31,920
He is well-acquainted with their poison.

350
00:38:33,400 --> 00:38:35,320
So he had us consume protective herbs beforehand.

351
00:38:39,200 --> 00:38:40,840
We took protective herbs?

352
00:38:42,160 --> 00:38:43,161
When was this?

353
00:38:48,360 --> 00:38:50,560
The liquor Grandfather granted us.

354
00:38:51,000 --> 00:38:52,960
Before we marched forth.

355
00:38:53,790 --> 00:38:56,920
It contained herbs that cure all poisons.

356
00:38:57,280 --> 00:39:00,560
I kept it from you to prevent overconfidence.

357
00:39:01,200 --> 00:39:02,400
So that you would remain vigilant.

358
00:39:04,543 --> 00:39:05,544
Water.

359
00:39:05,830 --> 00:39:07,440
Give me water.

360
00:39:07,543 --> 00:39:08,960
Give me water.

361
00:39:12,530 --> 00:39:13,531
Nares.

362
00:39:20,790 --> 00:39:23,320
I wasted my trust. Look at your brother.

363
00:39:23,610 --> 00:39:24,920
He fought until he was victorious.

364
00:39:25,150 --> 00:39:27,720
Beheading the Mohnyin general for Grandfather.

365
00:39:28,240 --> 00:39:30,280
Now look at you. What have you done?

366
00:39:31,863 --> 00:39:33,320
The Mohnyin general

367
00:39:34,350 --> 00:39:36,551
fell to that captive's blade, not Brother at all.

368
00:39:37,560 --> 00:39:38,960
I saw it myself.

369
00:39:40,600 --> 00:39:42,200
Brother barely survived that encounter.

370
00:39:44,150 --> 00:39:47,360
Prince Nares intervened and took the head with his twin swords.

371
00:39:48,710 --> 00:39:49,711
What?

372
00:39:50,400 --> 00:39:52,120
- Twin swords?
- Yes, Your Highness.

373
00:39:53,080 --> 00:39:55,400
His twin blades were a marvel.

374
00:39:56,320 --> 00:39:58,160
Swords spinning like chakrams.

375
00:39:59,080 --> 00:40:02,240
The Mohnyin's crossbow fire could not touch him.

376
00:40:13,783 --> 00:40:15,200
Without those swords,

377
00:40:16,040 --> 00:40:18,560
would our brother

378
00:40:19,241 --> 00:40:21,120
have stood a chance against the Mohnyin?

379
00:40:23,797 --> 00:40:24,898
Twin blades

380
00:40:26,320 --> 00:40:28,000
spinning like chakrams.

381
00:40:35,120 --> 00:40:36,320
Mon swords?

382
00:40:58,937 --> 00:41:01,080
My thanks to General Mingyi Swa,

383
00:41:01,710 --> 00:41:04,960
Vice-General Nares, and every soldier,

384
00:41:05,190 --> 00:41:08,280
for crushing the Mohnyin rebellion.

385
00:41:09,160 --> 00:41:10,680
For this great merit,

386
00:41:11,600 --> 00:41:13,800
I shall bestow rewards upon you all.

387
00:41:15,843 --> 00:41:17,560
- It is Your Majesty's great mercy.
- It is Your Majesty's great mercy.

388
00:41:21,120 --> 00:41:22,121
Your Majesty,

389
00:41:23,130 --> 00:41:26,760
I have heard the soldiers rumors of Prince Nares's marvel.

390
00:41:27,170 --> 00:41:29,800
He beheaded the Mohnyin general

391
00:41:30,143 --> 00:41:31,200
with his wondrous twin blades.

392
00:41:37,557 --> 00:41:39,080
Is that so, Nares?

393
00:41:43,957 --> 00:41:46,040
I am truly impressed by what I hear.

394
00:41:47,200 --> 00:41:50,120
Would Prince Nares be willing to demonstrate those twin blades?

395
00:41:50,150 --> 00:41:52,100
A sight for us to behold?

396
00:42:11,560 --> 00:42:14,400
To draw weapons before the throne

397
00:42:15,200 --> 00:42:17,150
might be unseemly at this hour, Your Majesty.

398
00:42:22,443 --> 00:42:24,000
For warriors like us,

399
00:42:25,520 --> 00:42:29,700
what is more beautiful than a soldier's skill?

400
00:42:41,103 --> 00:42:44,680
If your swordsmanship is truly so peerless,

401
00:42:45,480 --> 00:42:47,240
then please demonstrate it for us to see.

402
00:43:28,720 --> 00:43:31,880
The sword style you have learned from me is unlike any other.

403
00:43:32,640 --> 00:43:34,600
If you reveal it now,

404
00:43:35,200 --> 00:43:38,700
those who have seen me fight will surely recognize it.

405
00:43:39,240 --> 00:43:43,000
Especially King Bayinnaung, he must never see it.

406
00:44:42,683 --> 00:44:43,684
Enough!

407
00:44:49,690 --> 00:44:52,000
The twin sword style of Phra Maha Thera Khanchong.

408
00:44:52,903 --> 00:44:54,320
He has never taught it to anyone.

409
00:44:55,563 --> 00:44:57,280
I never imagined he would teach it to you.

410
00:45:03,870 --> 00:45:05,400
The Great Monk showed me mercy.

411
00:45:06,600 --> 00:45:08,480
Yet, His Holiness did not break his vow.

412
00:45:09,320 --> 00:45:10,700
While instructing me,

413
00:45:11,567 --> 00:45:14,052
his hands never once touched a blade, Your Majesty.

414
00:45:16,717 --> 00:45:17,718
Your Majesty,

415
00:45:18,600 --> 00:45:20,800
Prince Nares has learned the arts of the Mon.

416
00:45:21,401 --> 00:45:23,080
He consorts with those who harbor rebellion.

417
00:45:24,240 --> 00:45:27,360
Father, we must nip this in the bud. Strike now, before it is too late.

418
00:45:35,920 --> 00:45:36,921
Grandfather,

419
00:45:38,600 --> 00:45:42,200
these twin blades secured victory for Hongsawadi

420
00:45:43,400 --> 00:45:44,800
and saved my very life.

421
00:45:46,697 --> 00:45:48,920
Prince Nares has committed no wrong, Your Majesty.

422
00:45:49,043 --> 00:45:51,280
- But the law must be the law.
- Silence!

423
00:45:54,680 --> 00:45:58,080
A wise man should seek knowledge to empower himself.

424
00:46:00,290 --> 00:46:02,480
Learning the Mon style of swordsmanship is no crime.

425
00:46:05,843 --> 00:46:07,000
But it becomes a crime

426
00:46:08,040 --> 00:46:10,680
if one uses it to betray his friends.

427
00:46:21,880 --> 00:46:22,881
Prince Nares.

428
00:46:25,517 --> 00:46:27,920
I cherish you as my own kin.

429
00:46:29,000 --> 00:46:32,280
You are a dear friend to Mingyi Swa,

430
00:46:33,320 --> 00:46:36,400
just as I was to King Tabinshwehti.

431
00:46:37,560 --> 00:46:38,561
In the days to come,

432
00:46:39,317 --> 00:46:42,960
when Mingyi Swa ascends the throne of Hongsawadi,

433
00:46:43,520 --> 00:46:46,240
and you ascend the throne of Ayutthaya,

434
00:46:47,417 --> 00:46:50,120
it is my hope that our two kingdoms

435
00:46:51,120 --> 00:46:53,440
shall remain brotherly realms forevermore.

436
00:47:05,560 --> 00:47:07,001
I ask of you now,

437
00:47:08,320 --> 00:47:10,600
to swear before the sacred relics,

438
00:47:11,200 --> 00:47:13,473
that you will be a loyal friend for all time.

439
00:47:13,910 --> 00:47:15,560
Do you dare to take this oath?

440
00:47:23,560 --> 00:47:24,840
Let us swear this oath together.

441
00:47:26,360 --> 00:47:27,920
If you do not betray me,

442
00:47:28,920 --> 00:47:30,440
I shall not betray you.

443
00:47:31,443 --> 00:47:33,480
Do you agree?

444
00:48:02,750 --> 00:48:04,360
Someone has attempted to harm Prince Nares.

445
00:48:07,040 --> 00:48:10,057
How insolent! Does this kingdom have no law or order?

446
00:48:10,800 --> 00:48:12,760
You are like a thorn in the side of Jaisingh.

447
00:48:12,983 --> 00:48:15,280
In this life, the two of you can never share the same sky.

448
00:48:15,390 --> 00:48:17,120
Why, then, do you endure staying here?

449
00:48:17,190 --> 00:48:21,560
I was born but once, let me follow my heart.

450
00:48:23,577 --> 00:48:26,240
Remember me, elephant child?

451
00:48:26,520 --> 00:48:28,320
Tell Nares, to do this,

452
00:48:28,401 --> 00:48:29,920
is to commit treason against Hongsawadi.

453
00:48:30,000 --> 00:48:31,550
If you want my life, Brother,

454
00:48:32,503 --> 00:48:33,504
then come and take it.
